org.joda.primitives.collection.impl

Class ArrayByteCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.AbstractPrimitiveCollectable<Byte>
      • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.AbstractByteCollection
        • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.ArrayByteCollection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Iterable<Byte>, Collection<Byte>, ByteCollection, PrimitiveCollection<Byte>, ByteIterable, PrimitiveCollectable<Byte>

    public class ArrayByteCollection
extends AbstractByteCollection
implements Cloneable
    Array based implementation of ByteCollection for primitive byte elements.

    This collection implementation allows multiple copies of the same value to be added. Internally, it uses an array, and behaves much like a list.

    This class implements Collection allowing seamless integration with other APIs.

    Add, Remove and Clear are supported.

    Since:
    1.0

      • addAll

        public boolean addAll(byte startInclusive,
                      byte endInclusive)
        Adds a range of primitive values to this collection.

        The range is defined to be inclusive of the start and end. If the start is greater than the end then the range is equivalent to an empty collection.
